==Ancient Greek==

===Etymology===
*From [[κῦρος]] kyros (supremacy); supreme in authority, that is, (as noun) controller; by implication Mr. (as a respectful title):

===Pronunciation===
*κύριος kyrios key'-ree-os

===Noun===
:1: [[God]], [[Lord]]
:2: [[master]], [[chief]], [[proprietor]], [[owner]], [[possessor]]
:3: [[mister]], [[sir]], [[gentleman]]

===Adjective===
[[main]], [[major]], [[primary]], [[prime]], [[principal]]

